TY  - JOUR
AU  - Delatte, Anne-Laure
AU  - Fouquau, Julien
AU  - Portes, Richard
T1  - Regime-Dependent Sovereign Risk Pricing During the Euro Crisis*
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfw050
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 21
IS  - 1
SP  - 363
EP  - 385
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Previous work has documented a greater sensitivity of long-term government bond yields to fundamentals in euro area peripheral countries during the euro crisis, but we know little about the driver(s) of regime switches. Our estimates based on a panel smooth threshold regression model quantify and explain them: (1) investors have penalized a deterioration of fundamentals more strongly from 2010 to 2012; (2) the higher the bank credit risk, measured with the premium on credit derivatives, the higher the extra premium on fundamentals; (3) after ECB President Draghi’s speech in July 2012, it took 1 year to restore the noncrisis regime and suppress the extra premium.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfw050
ER  - 



